**README.md**

```markdown
# Curse Static Web Proxy

This proxy is designed to work fully for Vercel and static serverless sites.

## Deployment

To deploy the proxy to Vercel, follow these steps:

1. Create a new Vercel project.
2. Add the following code to your `vercel.json` file:

```json
{
  "routes": [
    {
      "src": "/api/:path*",
      "dest": "api/proxy.js"
    }
  ]
}
```

3. Deploy your project to Vercel.

## Configuration

The following configuration options are available:

- `port`: The port to listen on (default: 3000)
- `rateLimit.windowMs`: The time window in milliseconds for rate limiting (default: 1000)
- `rateLimit.max`: The maximum number of requests allowed per IP address within the time window (default: 10)
- `cache.stdTTL`: The standard time-to-live for cached responses in seconds (default: 600)

To change the configuration, edit the `config.js` file.

## Usage

To use the proxy, send a GET request to the following URL:

```
https://<your-vercel-project-url>/api/<path-to-resource>
```

For example, to proxy a request to the Vercel home page, you would send a GET request to the following URL:

```
https://<your-vercel-project-url>/api/https://vercel.com
```

## License

